detailedReviews.author: Michelle Mandich
detailedReviews.text: I have been a customer for 2 years now. I am not from Marion area. I started ordering because they deliver to my area. I ordered on 1/16 a chicken bacon sub for $14. With delivery fee it came to $18. I have previously ordered italian subs that were $11 no issue. I got a call telling me I had to order $6 more food to meet the minimum delivery. No where online does it state this. I asked her why because I never had to before and she said there has always been a minimum. She asked the manager why, then came back and said it was because they had other orders going my way. This is unacceptable and I should have cancelled my order. So instead of it costing me $22 (with tip because not drivers fault) its now over $30 for one person! Then to top it off the garlic cheese bread was not done and my sub was cold. They just lost a customer, as I will never order from them again.

detailedReviews.author: Hunter Merchant
detailedReviews.text: Pretty disappointed with Payne's this time around. Ordered an online order to be ready at 6:45pm at 6pm. We show up at 6:50 and it's not ready because they forgot to apparently check their online orders? Unclear. The kid at checkout was frazzled. We paid for a two topping (pepperoni and double cheese) pizza and received only burnt in the middle cheese pizza. It takes five seconds for a staff member to check the ticket and the toppings on the pizza before boxing it up. We didn't realize until we got home otherwise we would have had them fix it then and did not want to drive back out. I guess we will no longer be online ordering on the weekends anymore.

detailedReviews.author: Brad Church
detailedReviews.text:
We ordered a double cheese pepperoni  pizza for delivery tonight for the game.  We waiting an hour and 15 mins and a cheese only pizza was delivered.  Not what we ordered.

This was the saddest example of a pizza I have ever had delivered.  It was burnt, had more dough bubbles than cheese showing (cheese was sprayed on it was so thin) and the box weighed more than the pizza.

It is easy to see why this once great place to grab a pie has gone to trash.  Do NOT waste your money ordering from this rip off joint.

We hadn't tried Payne's before. So a couple of weeks ago we decided to. We have ordered from there 4 times! The service is awesome! The amount of food you get for the price is awesome! I got a chef salad and it had so much of the add ons that every bite of lettuce had something else with it! The best chef salad I have ever had! This has become our favorite place!
Update?!! 03/23/24
Ordered two sandwiches and a salad.waited over an hour and the guy has two sandwiches and no salad, then wants to argue with me about my order. I would not pay $24.50 for two sandwiches! Then he goes to his car comes back and wants me to pay for it and he will go get it and be back within the hour! No thanks! I sent the sandwiches back with him and told him we would not be ordering anymore! I had just told them on the phone I keep asking for pepperoni in my salad, being charged for it but it's not there! We was ordering 2 or 3 times a week! No more!
